# Backup snapshots excluded from image build
swanctl.bak.*/
*.bak-*

# StrongSwan swanctl/ config (operator-managed, bind-mounted at runtime)
# The live swanctl/ is mounted at /etc/swanctl/ when container runs.
# But the COPY in Dockerfile would add them to the image. Excluding
# keeps the image clean and uses bind-mount for runtime config.
# Actually NO - we DO need swanctl/ in the image for the start scripts
# to find confs. Don't exclude these.

# Actually re-evaluated: swanctl/ is BOTH copied into image AND bind-mounted
# at runtime. The COPY happens at build time, providing defaults; the
# bind-mount at runtime overrides with operator-specific configs.
# So we MUST include swanctl/ in image, and EXCLUDE only the .bak snapshots.
